102
00:11:27,563 --> 00:11:30,816
{y:i}[Woman]{y}
{y:i}It was confirmed{y}
{y:i}two seasons back.{y} Y{y:i}es.{y}

103
00:11:30,899 --> 00:11:33,235
{y:i}[Woman #2]{y}
{y:i}They're coming here.{y}
{y:i}I mean, are we next?{y}

104
00:11:33,277 --> 00:11:35,279
{y:i}[Man]{y}
{y:i}Militants storm...{y}

105
00:11:35,362 --> 00:11:38,490
{y:i}[Woman #3]{y}
Y{y:i}es. But going to the underground{y}
{y:i}shelters if it happens...{y}

106
00:11:38,574 --> 00:11:40,742
{y:i}[Man #2]{y}
Y{y:i}ou're right.{y}
{y:i}That's what I thought too.{y}

107
00:11:40,826 --> 00:11:43,287
{y:i}[Man #3]{y}
{y:i}Are you staying or leaving?{y}

108
00:11:43,370 --> 00:11:45,706
{y:i}[Man #4]{y}
{y:i}It's the end of everything.{y}
{y:i}Everything.!{y}

109
00:11:45,789 --> 00:11:49,251
{y:i}[Man #5] Well, my neighbors...{y}
{y:i}[Man #6]{y}
{y:i}Half my street is gone.{y}

110
00:11:49,334 --> 00:11:51,253
What are we gonna do?
I don't know. I don't know.

111
00:11:51,295 --> 00:11:53,255
{y:i}[Woman #4]{y}
{y:i}Hood of the devil.{y}
{y:i}That's what someone called 'em.{y}

112
00:11:53,297 --> 00:11:55,424
Them? Who is them?
Some kind of new creature...

113
00:11:55,465 --> 00:11:57,467
This is nonsense.
It's all nonsense.

114
00:11:57,551 --> 00:12:01,471
{y:i}[Man #7]{y}
{y:i}So tall that it touches the clouds.{y}

115
00:12:01,513 --> 00:12:05,893
And there's nothing around
this statue, this colossus.
Nothing left.

116
00:12:05,976 --> 00:12:08,187
It's their calling card.

117
00:12:18,655 --> 00:12:21,867
{y:i}[Riddick]{y}
{y:i}Did you know all your doors were locked?{y}

118
00:12:26,955 --> 00:12:29,333
{y:i}Five years ago,{y}

119
00:12:29,374 --> 00:12:32,294
{y:i}I took two people off that planet...{y}

120
00:12:32,336 --> 00:12:36,590
{y:i}A kid, Jack,{y}
{y:i}who everyone else thought was a boy, ;{y}

121
00:12:36,673 --> 00:12:39,343
{y:i}and a holy man...{y}

122
00:12:39,426 --> 00:12:41,345
{y:i}searching for New Mecca.{y}

123
00:12:44,890 --> 00:12:46,975
Y{y:i}our wife...{y}

124
00:12:48,894 --> 00:12:50,896
She's in the shower.

125
00:12:50,979 --> 00:12:55,943
{y:i}I told one man...{y}

126
00:12:56,026 --> 00:12:59,154
where I might go.

127
00:12:59,238 --> 00:13:03,200
I showed trust to one man.

128
00:13:03,242 --> 00:13:06,745
Did I make a mistake, Imam?

129
00:13:06,828 --> 00:13:09,164
There is no simple answer.

130
00:13:09,206 --> 00:13:13,919
Whatever was said
was meant to give us a chance...

131
00:13:14,002 --> 00:13:16,004
a fighting chance.

132
00:13:17,381 --> 00:13:20,717
Were it not for the threat of invasion,
I never would have betrayed you.

133
00:13:20,801 --> 00:13:24,012
{y:i}I give you my word, Riddick.{y}
Riddick!

134
00:13:25,055 --> 00:13:27,057
Riddick!

135
00:13:29,977 --> 00:13:32,479
{y:i}[Riddick]{y}
{y:i}And a daughter...{y}

136
00:13:33,939 --> 00:13:37,025
- No!
- Whose name would be...

137
00:13:37,109 --> 00:13:39,695
If you have issue with me,
you let it be with me.

138
00:13:39,736 --> 00:13:42,239
You need not know their names.
{y:i}[Girl]{y}
{y:i}Ziza.{y}

139
00:13:44,449 --> 00:13:46,368
My name is Ziza.

140
00:13:47,661 --> 00:13:49,580
Ziza.

141
00:13:51,290 --> 00:13:55,294
- Cute kid.
{y:i}- Did you really kill monsters?{y}

142
00:13:55,377 --> 00:13:57,880
The ones that were gonna
hurt my father?

143
00:13:59,756 --> 00:14:01,884
Such are our bedtime stories.

144
00:14:01,925 --> 00:14:04,636
Go, Ziza. Go on!

145
00:14:09,683 --> 00:14:13,812
