That is what you had in mind,
right, Toombs?

437
00:46:36,755 --> 00:46:40,384
- Hey, how does he know
where we're goin', and we don't?
- Dope it out.

438
00:46:40,467 --> 00:46:43,220
- I hate this run.
- Just do it!

439
00:46:43,303 --> 00:46:45,973
Don't know about this
new crew of yours.

440
00:46:46,056 --> 00:46:49,351
They seem a bit skittish.

441
00:46:49,434 --> 00:46:52,980
Probably shouldn't tell 'em
what happened to the last crew.

442
00:47:00,696 --> 00:47:05,158
You know, you supposed
to be some slick-shit killer.

443
00:47:05,242 --> 00:47:07,786
Now look at you...

444
00:47:07,870 --> 00:47:11,039
all back-of-the-bus
and shit.

445
00:47:47,618 --> 00:47:50,245
{y:i}I say we attack Helion Two next.{y}

446
00:47:50,329 --> 00:47:52,247
Take it straight
into their teeth.

447
00:47:52,331 --> 00:47:55,751
It'll cost you 20,000 heads,
five warrior ships.
Nothing more, I swear it.

448
00:47:55,792 --> 00:47:59,129
While I do prize brute force,

449
00:47:59,213 --> 00:48:02,341
this approach
is perhaps more artful.

450
00:48:02,424 --> 00:48:05,260
Start at the end.

451
00:48:05,302 --> 00:48:07,304
Go straight to Helion Five,

452
00:48:07,387 --> 00:48:09,598
the last planet
in the system.

453
00:48:09,640 --> 00:48:12,267
We approach from the night side.

454
00:48:12,351 --> 00:48:15,312
{y:i}Remove these cannon first,{y}

455
00:48:15,395 --> 00:48:18,232
then attack
the larger placements at speed.

456
00:48:18,315 --> 00:48:21,109
{y:i}We'll catch them on their rear flank.{y}
{y:i}And in ten days'time,{y}

457
00:48:21,151 --> 00:48:25,489
{y:i}the rest of those worlds{y}
{y:i}will tumble before us.{y}

458
00:48:25,572 --> 00:48:27,908
You see, as with most,
their blind spot...

459
00:48:27,991 --> 00:48:30,285
is right behind them.

460
00:48:32,329 --> 00:48:35,916
I've located an ion trail
which leads off-world.

461
00:48:35,999 --> 00:48:38,669
Then you should be
off-world, Vaako.

462
00:48:38,752 --> 00:48:41,338
I've deployed a tracker team.
One of the best.

463
00:48:41,421 --> 00:48:45,133
Wherever Riddick has gone,
you lens him out and cleanse him.

464
00:48:46,176 --> 00:48:50,097
- You.
- You want me to take a frigate
for one breeder?

465
00:48:50,180 --> 00:48:52,266
Don't question it, Vaako!

466
00:48:54,184 --> 00:48:57,354
Take it on faith.

467
00:49:00,524 --> 00:49:03,944
He's always been unsettled around you...

468
00:49:04,027 --> 00:49:06,029
the Lord Marshal.

469
00:49:06,113 --> 00:49:08,991
Unsteady.

470
00:49:09,074 --> 00:49:12,744
Perhaps because he knows
he's half the warrior you are.

471
00:49:12,828 --> 00:49:15,873
{y:i}Some say he's too artistic{y}
{y:i}for thejob.{y}

472
00:49:17,374 --> 00:49:20,002
I wouldn't be surprised
if someone promoted him soon...

473
00:49:20,085 --> 00:49:23,005
{y:i}to full dead.{y}

474
00:49:25,424 --> 00:49:27,342
Take care what you say.

475
00:49:27,426 --> 00:49:30,345
Should I say it softly?

476
00:49:30,387 --> 00:49:33,348
So it sounds more
like conspiracy?

477
00:49:33,432 --> 00:49:37,269
Oh, why is it that when anyone
breathes about the demise of him
on the throne...

478
00:49:37,352 --> 00:49:40,022
everyone assumes
a conspiracy?

479
00:49:41,732 --> 00:49:45,068
Why isn't that
just prudent planning?

480
00:49:45,152 --> 00:49:47,654
When he is ready,
he will name a successor.

481
00:49:47,738 --> 00:49:49,823
Who?

482
00:49:49,907 --> 00:49:54,203
Toal? Scales? The Purifier?

483
00:49:54,244 --> 00:49:56,580
None of them...

484
00:49:56,663 --> 00:49:59,416
with the strength,
the dignity,

485
00:49:59,499 --> 00:50:03,587
of Lord Vaako.

486
00:50:03,670 --> 00:50:05,881
You can keep what you kill.

487
00:50:05,964 --> 00:50:09,218
- Stop.
- That is the Necromonger way.

488
00:50:09,301 --> 00:50:12,846
I said... stop.
[Grunts]

489
00:50:12,930 --> 00:50:16,308
His death will come in due time
and not a moment sooner.

490
00:50:16,391 --> 00:50:19,978
- Why?
- Because I se{y:i}rv{y}e him. We all se{y:i}rv{y}e him.
It's called fidelity.

491
00:50:20,062 --> 00:50:22,231
It's called stupidity.

492
00:50:22,272 --> 00:50:25,067
[Laughs]

493
00:50:26,235 --> 00:50:28,570
{y:i}[Cries Out]{y}

494
00:50:31,281 --> 00:50:33,283
Well, finally some attention.

495
00:50:33,367 --> 00:50:35,577
{y:i}[Screams]{y}

496
00:50:35,619 --> 00:50:38,664
[Both Grunting, Screaming]

497
00:50:43,794 --> 00:50:46,129
[Moaning]

498
00:50:46,213 --> 00:50:50,092
You have such greatness in you.

499
00:50:50,133 --> 00:50:52,261
If only you could see it like I do.

500
00:50:55,138 --> 00:50:57,182
You know what I want?

501
00:50:58,809 --> 00:51:02,855
Today I came up behind him
in perfect silence and he knew.

502
00:51:02,938 --> 00:51:05,357
I wanna go down
in Necropolis.

503
00:51:07,276 --> 00:51:09,236
Right now.

504
00:51:09,319 --> 00:51:14,366
His half-dead soul sensed I was
behind him. He sees everything.

505
00:51:14,449 --> 00:51:16,618
When no one is looking...

506
00:51:16,702 --> 00:51:19,246
when no one's around...

507
00:51:19,329 --> 00:51:21,623
I'm gonna get down on my knees...

508
00:51:23,333 --> 00:51:26,795
while you sit on the throne.

509
00:51:31,258 --> 00:51:34,303
{y:i}[Indistinct Conversation]{y}

510
00:51:49,026 --> 00:51:52,821
- [Lord Marshal] How unexpected.
- An Elemental.

511
00:51:52,905 --> 00:51:56,491
{y:i}Here.{y}
{y:i}One of the captives.{y}

512
00:51:56,575 --> 00:51:59,494
{y:i}[Lord Marshal]{y}
{y:i}And why, after 30 years,{y}

513
00:51:59,578 --> 00:52:01,830
should it be you?

514
00:52:01,872 --> 00:52:04,291
He doesn't regard her
as a captive, though.

515
00:52:04,374 --> 00:52:07,169
{y:i}Elementals...{y}
{y:i}they talk of neutrality,{y}

516
00:52:07,211 --> 00:52:09,213
{y:i}but they're all witches{y}
{y:i}and spies.{y}

517
00:52:09,296 --> 00:52:12,216
{y:i}Why else would they{y}
{y:i}come and go like the wind?{y}

518
00:52:12,299 --> 00:52:16,303
But where has he gone?
Where is the Furyan hiding now?

519
00:52:16,386 --> 00:52:19,348
You be the good warrior.

520
00:52:19,389 --> 00:52:22,309
Go after this Riddick.

521
00:52:22,392 --> 00:52:26,021
I'll find out why the Lord Marshal
is so threatened by him.

522
00:53:03,851 --> 00:53:05,894
{y:i}[Creaking]{y}

523
00:53:25,289 --> 00:53:29,251
{y:i}[Panting]{y}
Do you know
you grind your teeth at night?

524
00:53:31,044 --> 00:53:32,754
Sexy.

525
00:53:34,256 --> 00:53:36,216
[Grunts]

526
00:53:48,979 --> 00:53:51,440
{y:i}[Female Computer Voice]{y}
{y:i}Destination reached.{y}

527
00:53:51,481 --> 00:53:53,442
{y:i}Unlocking manual controls.{y}

528
00:53:53,483 --> 00:53:56,862
All right. I make 700 degrees
on the day side,

529
00:53:56,945 --> 00:53:58,906
300 below on the night side.

530
00:53:58,989 --> 00:54:01,950
Let's not get caught in the sun.

531
00:54:01,992 --> 00:54:04,453
If I owned this place and hell,

532
00:54:04,494 --> 00:54:07,497
I'd rent this place out
and live in hell.

533
00:54:16,256 --> 00:54:18,634
{y:i}- [Female Computer Voice]{y}
{y:i}Blue angle... good.{y}
- Stand by.

534
00:54:20,177 --> 00:54:22,137
{y:i}And...{y}

535
00:54:22,221 --> 00:54:24,139
{y:i}[Female Computer Voice]{y}
{y:i}Plotted course good.{y}

536
00:54:24,223 --> 00:54:26,642
Hit it!

537
00:54:26,683 --> 00:54:30,521
{y:i}[Female Computer Voice]{y}
{y:i}Angle of approach, not good.{y}

538
00:54:37,861 --> 00:54:40,572
- [Laughing]
{y:i}- Look, Ma. No hands.!{y}

539
00:54:40,656 --> 00:54:43,408
{y:i}[Shouting, Laughing]{y}

540
00:55:15,023 --> 00:55:16,942
Party poppers!

541
00:55:39,381 --> 00:55:41,717
I think I shit myself.

542
00:55:42,968 --> 00:55:46,138
Skittish, Toombs. Very skittish.

543
00:56:07,659 --> 00:56:09,578
Comry?

544
00:56:27,054 --> 00:56:30,432
When the ride's over,

545
00:56:30,474 --> 00:56:33,060
your goggles are mine.

546
00:56:53,330 --> 00:56:55,499
[Groaning]

547
00:57:01,630 --> 00:57:04,675
Four-way split!
[Laughing]

548
00:57:15,018 --> 00:57:17,312
29.4 kilometers.

549
00:57:25,821 --> 00:57:30,158
So, this is Riddick.

550
00:57:54,808 --> 00:57:58,812
What in the bowels of Christ
are you talkin' about, 700K?

551
00:57:58,896 --> 00:58:00,814
Don't take this one, boss.

552
00:58:00,898 --> 00:58:04,193
See? Anatoli here
has a nose for trouble.

553
00:58:04,234 --> 00:58:06,612
And this one, this Riddick guy...

554
00:58:06,695 --> 00:58:08,780
Big, big trouble.

555
00:58:08,864 --> 00:58:11,992
So, 700,000 is good money.

556
00:58:12,075 --> 00:58:15,829
I'd take the money, Toombs.

557
00:58:23,545 --> 00:58:28,050
{y:i}[Clanging]{y}
The guild pays us a caretaker's fee
for each prisoner each year.

558
00:58:28,133 --> 00:58:32,179
We pay mercs 20% of that total fee
based on a certain life expectancy.

559
00:58:32,262 --> 00:58:33,889
{y:i}How's about this?{y}

560
00:58:33,931 --> 00:58:36,892
You open that safe you got hidden
behind the console there,

561
00:58:36,934 --> 00:58:41,063
{y:i}show me the real books,{y}
{y:i}then we{y} f{y:i}igure out my cut.{y}

562
00:58:41,146 --> 00:58:43,148
{y:i}Then I'll be on my way.{y}

563
00:58:48,028 --> 00:58:51,406
{y:i}Open my books.{y}
{y:i}This is what you suggest?{y}

564
00:58:56,411 --> 00:58:58,413
Wasn't a suggestion.

565
00:59:00,541 --> 00:59:02,709
{y:i}[Clanging Continues]{y}

566
00:59:07,798 --> 00:59:09,925
{y:i}[Clanging Continues]{y}

567
00:59:16,306 --> 00:59:21,019
{y:i}These are dangerous days,{y}
{y:i}if you believe the talk.{y}

568
00:59:22,020 --> 00:59:25,065
Talk?
About dead planets.

569
00:59:25,148 --> 00:59:28,277
About some ghost army.

570
00:59:28,318 --> 00:59:30,988
About them.

571
00:59:31,071 --> 00:59:34,491
"Them"?
[Scoffs]

572
00:59:51,300 --> 00:59:53,218
I'll run the numbers again.

573
00:59:53,302 --> 00:59:55,387
It takes a couple of days,
probably,

574
00:59:55,470 --> 00:59:58,849
so you can stay as my guest.

575
00:59:58,932 --> 01:00:00,851
At least here, we are all safe.

576
01:00:00,934 --> 01:00:04,229
Yes?
{y:i}[Man]{y}
Y{y:i}es, boss.{y}

577
01:00:04,313 --> 01:00:06,690
I'll give it a day.

578
01:00:09,026 --> 01:00:11,153
One.

579
01:00:49,608 --> 01:00:51,527
{y:i}[Man]{y}
{y:i}There are inmates...{y}

580
01:00:51,610 --> 01:00:54,363
{y:i}and there are convicts.{y}

581
01:00:54,404 --> 01:00:57,866
A convict has a certain code.

582
01:00:57,950 --> 01:01:01,870
And he knows to show
a certain respect.

583
01:01:02,955 --> 01:01:05,499
{y:i}An inmate, on the other hand,{y}

584
01:01:05,541 --> 01:01:08,085
pulls the pin on his fellow man.

585
01:01:08,168 --> 01:01:10,546
{y:i}Does the guards'work for them.{y}

586
01:01:10,629 --> 01:01:13,215
- Brings shame...
- [Shouts]

587
01:01:13,298 --> 01:01:15,676
To the game.

588
01:01:17,678 --> 01:01:20,639
So, which are you gonna be?

589
01:01:20,722 --> 01:01:23,225
Me?

590
01:01:25,352 --> 01:01:27,646
I'm just passin' through.

591
01:01:33,443 --> 01:01:35,612
Welcome to Crematoria.

592
01:01:41,785 --> 01:01:44,246
Should I go for the sweet spot?

593
01:01:44,288 --> 01:01:47,916
Left of the spine, fourth lumbar down,
the abdominal aorta.

594
01:01:48,000 --> 01:01:50,419
What a gusher.

595
01:01:52,754 --> 01:01:54,715
How do I get eyes like that?

596
01:01:54,798 --> 01:01:57,176
You gotta kill a few people.

597
01:01:57,259 --> 01:01:59,428
[Chuckles]
Did that.

598
01:01:59,469 --> 01:02:01,305
Did a lot of that.

599
01:02:02,931 --> 01:02:06,685
And then you gotta get sent to a slam.
One where they tell you you'll
never see daylight again?

600
01:02:06,768 --> 01:02:10,355
Only there wasn't any doctor here
who could shine my eyes,
not even for 20 menthol Kools.

601
01:02:10,439 --> 01:02:12,524
Was there anything
you said that was true?

602
01:02:15,319 --> 01:02:18,530
What are you gonna do, huh?
Go for the sweet spot?

603
01:02:18,614 --> 01:02:21,950
Remember who
you're talkin' to, Jack.

604
01:02:23,702 --> 01:02:27,039
Jack's dead.
She was weak.

605
01:02:28,207 --> 01:02:30,667
She couldn't cut it.

606
01:02:43,805 --> 01:02:45,974
The name's Kyra now.

607
01:02:46,058 --> 01:02:48,018
And I'm a new animal.

608
01:03:24,304 --> 01:03:28,976
They can be quite a test,
these deep runs...

609
01:03:30,811 --> 01:03:32,980
tests of our inner selves.

610
01:03:35,315 --> 01:03:37,693
Don't you find that true?

611
01:03:41,280 --> 01:03:43,282
Some men do.

612
01:03:44,700 --> 01:03:47,202
{y:i}Just being so far from the armada,{y}

613
01:03:47,286 --> 01:03:53,166
the mind can start to fill
with strange thoughts, doubts.

614
01:03:53,250 --> 01:03:56,170
Don't you ever have doubts, Vaako?

615
01:03:59,631 --> 01:04:02,092
- Doubts?
- About the campaign.

616
01:04:03,135 --> 01:04:05,262
About Lord Marshal.

617
01:04:07,306 --> 01:04:11,643
First and always,
I am a Necromonger commander.

618
01:04:12,728 --> 01:04:17,816
So if you're here to test my loyalty,
you succeed only in testing my patience.

619
01:04:17,900 --> 01:04:21,486
Oh, no.
No, that's not why I'm here at all.

620
01:04:42,925 --> 01:04:45,636
{y:i}[Dame Vaako]{y}
{y:i}I'm so glad I could{y}
{y:i}steal you away for a moment.{y}

621
01:04:45,677 --> 01:04:48,096
Doesn't it strike you odd?

622
01:04:48,180 --> 01:04:50,807
{y:i}Here we have{y}
{y:i}the current Lord Marshal...{y}

623
01:04:50,849 --> 01:04:54,978
{y:i}destroying entire societies,{y}
{y:i}and yet he can't bring himself...{y}

624
01:04:55,020 --> 01:04:58,982
to kill one
stranded Elemental.

625
01:04:59,066 --> 01:05:01,026
Why is that?

626
01:05:02,194 --> 01:05:04,154
You don't pray to our god.

627
01:05:04,196 --> 01:05:06,782
You pray to no god, I hear.

628
01:05:06,865 --> 01:05:09,826
Elementals... we calculate.

629
01:05:10,911 --> 01:05:12,871
Don't we all.

630
01:05:12,913 --> 01:05:16,834
But now let's have first things first.

631
01:05:16,875 --> 01:05:20,128
What of Riddick?
In truth, I don't know
where he went.

632
01:05:20,212 --> 01:05:23,131
In truth, I'm more interested
in where he came from.

633
01:05:25,259 --> 01:05:27,511
Watch your step.

634
01:05:27,553 --> 01:05:30,264
I've always wondered,

635
01:05:30,347 --> 01:05:32,933
does an air Elemental fly?

636
01:05:33,016 --> 01:05:35,018
{y:i}Now do me a favor.{y}

637
01:05:35,060 --> 01:05:39,022
Calculate the odds of you
getting off this planet alive...

638
01:05:39,106 --> 01:05:41,108
and now cut them in half.

639
01:05:42,568 --> 01:05:44,486
No, we can't fly.

640
01:05:44,570 --> 01:05:47,030
But we glide very well.

641
01:05:47,072 --> 01:05:49,867
{y:i}Save your threats, Necromonger.{y}

642
01:05:50,951 --> 01:05:54,538
I would have told you about Riddick
for the asking.

643
01:05:54,580 --> 01:05:58,375
It concerns a foretelling,
a prediction now more than 30 years old.

644
01:05:58,458 --> 01:06:02,754
{y:i}Ayoung warrior{y}
{y:i}once consulted a seer.{y}

645
01:06:02,838 --> 01:06:07,885
{y:i}He was told a child would be born{y}
{y:i}on the planet Furya... a male child...{y}

646
01:06:07,968 --> 01:06:12,389
{y:i}who would someday{y}
{y:i}cause the warrior's downfall.{y}

647
01:06:12,431 --> 01:06:16,059
{y:i}[Female Voice]{y}
{y:i}Cause his untimed death.{y}

648
01:06:17,060 --> 01:06:22,024
Furya? Furya's a ruined world.
No life to speak of.

649
01:06:22,107 --> 01:06:23,650
For good reason.

650
01:06:23,734 --> 01:06:28,739
This young warrior
mounted an attack on Furya,

651
01:06:28,780 --> 01:06:31,909
killing all young males
he could find,

652
01:06:31,950 --> 01:06:36,079
even strangling some
with their birth cords.

653
01:06:36,121 --> 01:06:38,916
An artful stroke,
wouldn't you say?

654
01:06:40,834 --> 01:06:44,880
So this warrior, the one
who tried to outwit the prediction,
would later become...

655
01:06:44,963 --> 01:06:46,965
That's why he worries.

656
01:06:47,049 --> 01:06:49,051
The Lord Marshal.

657
01:06:50,636 --> 01:06:52,638
Which would make
the man-child...

658
01:06:52,721 --> 01:06:55,182
He worries he missed
killing that child in its crib.

659
01:06:55,265 --> 01:06:57,226
Riddick.

660
01:06:57,309 --> 01:07:00,229
{y:i}[Baby Crying]{y}

661
01:07:14,284 --> 01:07:16,453
{y:i}That's why it's so vital to him.{y}
Wait.

662
01:07:16,495 --> 01:07:18,914
{y:i}- It's about a prophecy.{y}
- Wait! Wait!

663
01:07:21,959 --> 01:07:23,961
Are you there?

664
01:07:27,506 --> 01:07:29,883
You do what your lord asks.

665
01:07:29,967 --> 01:07:33,637
You cleanse Riddick for him,
and in doing so...

666
01:07:33,679 --> 01:07:37,099
you prove your undying loyalty.

667
01:07:37,182 --> 01:07:42,813
And perhaps then
he'll finally let down his guard.

668
01:08:25,564 --> 01:08:27,107
{y:i}[Man]{y}
{y:i}Still here, I see?{y}

669
01:08:27,191 --> 01:08:30,903
I've been here 18 years.
See this?

670
01:08:32,988 --> 01:08:38,827
I remember how gorgeous she was.
