- [Grunts]

911
01:37:32,352 --> 01:37:34,271
{y:i}[Kyra]{y}
{y:i}No.!{y}

912
01:37:47,159 --> 01:37:49,912
- [Yells]
- [Grunts]

913
01:37:53,207 --> 01:37:56,251
[Grunting]

914
01:37:56,335 --> 01:37:58,545
Aaah!

915
01:38:05,344 --> 01:38:09,264
[Gasping, Groaning]

916
01:38:11,225 --> 01:38:12,851
[Yells]

917
01:38:16,230 --> 01:38:18,941
{y:i}Get up. Get up.!{y}

918
01:38:19,024 --> 01:38:20,984
{y:i}Please get up.{y}

919
01:38:34,289 --> 01:38:35,958
{y:i}So,{y}

920
01:38:37,876 --> 01:38:40,671
you can kneel.

921
01:38:58,105 --> 01:39:00,607
{y:i}[Woman's Voice, Distorted]{y}
{y:i}I think you know now.{y}

922
01:39:02,276 --> 01:39:04,695
I think you know
who tore Furya apart.

923
01:39:08,073 --> 01:39:11,577
This mark carries the anger
of an entire race.

924
01:39:11,660 --> 01:39:13,871
[Inhales]

925
01:39:16,915 --> 01:39:19,042
But it's going to hurt.

926
01:40:16,475 --> 01:40:18,435
[Groaning]

927
01:40:18,519 --> 01:40:20,521
[Groans]

928
01:40:22,814 --> 01:40:25,943
{y:i}[Wind Whistling]{y}
{y:i}[Engines Thrumming]{y}

929
01:40:33,325 --> 01:40:36,620
{y:i}[Alarm Siren]{y}

930
01:41:15,993 --> 01:41:17,953
[Gasps]

931
01:41:21,373 --> 01:41:24,376
{y:i}[Soft Clatter]{y}

932
01:41:36,889 --> 01:41:39,099
Kyra?

933
01:41:42,978 --> 01:41:45,898
{y:i}I was supposed to{y}
{y:i}deliver a message to you...{y}

934
01:41:47,900 --> 01:41:50,194
if Vaako failed to kill you.

935
01:41:52,070 --> 01:41:54,865
A message from
the Lord Marshal himself.

936
01:41:56,742 --> 01:42:00,245
He tells you to stay away from Helion,
stay away from him,

937
01:42:01,580 --> 01:42:03,707
and in return,
you'll be hunted no more.

938
01:42:10,714 --> 01:42:13,550
But Vaako will most likely
report you as dead.

939
01:42:14,927 --> 01:42:17,221
So this is your chance.

940
01:42:17,262 --> 01:42:21,058
Your chance to do
what no man has ever done.

941
01:42:21,099 --> 01:42:23,101
The girl.

942
01:42:24,102 --> 01:42:26,313
Where will they take her?

943
01:42:26,396 --> 01:42:29,358
[Gasping]

944
01:42:43,288 --> 01:42:46,625
We all began... as something else.

945
01:42:50,879 --> 01:42:55,467
I've done... unbelievable things...

946
01:42:56,468 --> 01:42:59,263
in the name of a faith
that was never my own.

947
01:43:01,139 --> 01:43:05,102
And he'll do to her
what he did to me.

948
01:43:11,358 --> 01:43:15,988
The Necromonger in me
warns you not to go back.

949
01:43:17,322 --> 01:43:19,950
But the Furyan in me...

950
01:43:23,495 --> 01:43:25,247
hopes you won't listen.

951
01:43:31,086 --> 01:43:35,757
God knows... I've dreamed of it.

952
01:44:36,944 --> 01:44:39,821
{y:i}I have lost a Purifier...{y}

953
01:44:41,073 --> 01:44:45,869
{y:i}but I have gained{y}
{y:i}a first among commanders.{y}

954
01:44:46,870 --> 01:44:49,498
It is overdue, isn't it...

955
01:44:49,581 --> 01:44:52,251
that we acknowledge
your many accomplishments,

956
01:44:52,334 --> 01:44:54,503
{y:i}your steady faith,{y}

957
01:44:54,586 --> 01:45:00,092
and above all,
your unflinching loyalty.

958
01:45:07,850 --> 01:45:11,353
Obedience without question.
Loyalty till UnderVerse come.

959
01:45:13,856 --> 01:45:15,858
Well done, Vaako.

960
01:45:17,109 --> 01:45:20,737
This is a day of days.

961
01:45:40,507 --> 01:45:43,051
Look more pleased, Vaako.

962
01:45:44,803 --> 01:45:48,223
You have killed his enemy...

963
01:45:48,307 --> 01:45:50,058
and his suspicions.

964
01:45:50,142 --> 01:45:54,938
- I should have brought back his head.
- You saw him unbreathing.
You saw him dead on the ground.

965
01:45:54,980 --> 01:45:57,983
Riddick was no common breeder.
In a heartbeat he dropped 20 of my men.

966
01:45:58,066 --> 01:46:02,029
All mysteries are not miracles,
not even in this religion.

967
01:46:04,531 --> 01:46:07,117
And if you say it is certain,
then it is certain,

968
01:46:07,201 --> 01:46:10,495
and we've already said it,
haven't we?

969
01:46:13,165 --> 01:46:15,125
We have.

970
01:46:17,211 --> 01:46:18,837
{y:i}[Door Opens]{y}

971
01:46:18,921 --> 01:46:21,423
{y:i}Now, tell me if it's true.{y}

972
01:46:21,507 --> 01:46:25,761
Tell me the Furyan is gone,
and I can close this campaign
without hearing his bootsteps.

973
01:46:27,262 --> 01:46:29,264
If he is dead,

974
01:46:30,432 --> 01:46:32,434
I sense I'm not far
from the same fate,

975
01:46:33,519 --> 01:46:35,479
being of no further use here.

976
01:46:36,522 --> 01:46:39,608
Shouldn't I tell you
that Riddick is still alive?

977
01:46:39,691 --> 01:46:41,485
Don't try me, Aereon.

978
01:46:41,527 --> 01:46:43,820
I could plow you under
with the rest of Helion Prime.

979
01:46:43,862 --> 01:46:46,198
No one really knows the future.

980
01:46:46,281 --> 01:46:50,077
Then tell me the odds
that Vaako met with success,

981
01:46:50,160 --> 01:46:52,120
that I will now be the one...

982
01:46:52,204 --> 01:46:55,123
who can carry his people across
the threshold into UnderVerse,

983
01:46:55,165 --> 01:46:57,167
where they shall begin true life.

984
01:46:57,251 --> 01:46:59,545
Tell me what I want to hear, Aereon,

985
01:46:59,628 --> 01:47:03,715
and maybe
I'll save your home world... for last.

986
01:47:08,554 --> 01:47:11,056
- The odds are good...
- That?

987
01:47:11,139 --> 01:47:13,684
That you will reach the UnderVerse...

988
01:47:16,895 --> 01:47:18,897
{y:i}soon.{y}

989
01:47:57,269 --> 01:47:59,062
Ascension protocol!

990
01:47:59,146 --> 01:48:02,858
We still have numbers
out there, Lord Marshal...
sweep teams, recon ships.

991
01:48:02,941 --> 01:48:04,985
They would be hard-pressed
to make it back...

992
01:48:09,781 --> 01:48:13,577
Get my armada off the ground!

993
01:48:16,371 --> 01:48:19,041
{y:i}[Engines Thrumming]{y}
{y:i}[Large Machinery Noises]{y}

994
01:48:47,152 --> 01:48:49,905
[Chattering]

995
01:48:53,492 --> 01:48:54,993
[Heavy Slam]

996
01:49:02,251 --> 01:49:04,419
- [Chattering Continues]
- [Heavy Slam]

997
01:49:15,138 --> 01:49:18,684
- You mean on Helion?
- I mean here, on this very ship!

998
01:49:18,767 --> 01:49:23,063
Could you be wrong?
Mind fabricates fear.

999
01:49:23,146 --> 01:49:27,401
Could you be wrong?
Not so wrong as you
when you left him alive!

1000
01:49:27,484 --> 01:49:29,403
It's twice a mistake.

1001
01:49:29,486 --> 01:49:32,739
Not only your failure,
but now the report of success.

1002
01:49:32,823 --> 01:49:36,410
How do we salvage this? How? How?

1003
01:49:36,493 --> 01:49:39,037
Lord Marshal's got to be warned.

1004
01:49:39,121 --> 01:49:41,039
You will never see the UnderVerse!

1005
01:49:42,374 --> 01:49:44,501
He will kill us both
before our due time.

1006
01:49:47,671 --> 01:49:49,590
I say give Riddick his chance.

1007
01:49:54,428 --> 01:49:57,014
If he is half of what you think,

1008
01:49:57,097 --> 01:49:59,141
he can at least wound the Lord Marshal...

1009
01:49:59,224 --> 01:50:01,685
and that is when you must act.

1010
01:50:01,768 --> 01:50:04,146
Just to take his place?
Just to keep what I kill?

1011
01:50:04,229 --> 01:50:06,940
- That is the Necromonger way.
- It is not enough!

1012
01:50:07,024 --> 01:50:09,776
Then you do it for the faith!

1013
01:50:09,860 --> 01:50:12,571
If he has fear, he has weakness.

1014
01:50:12,654 --> 01:50:14,573
If he has weakness, Vaako...

1015
01:50:16,617 --> 01:50:18,785
He is unworthy of lordship.

1016
01:50:19,786 --> 01:50:22,122
We do it for all Necromongers.

1017
01:50:23,624 --> 01:50:25,792
Protect the faith.

1018
01:50:25,876 --> 01:50:28,879
This can still be a day of days,

1019
01:50:28,962 --> 01:50:31,048
but the timing...

1020
01:50:31,131 --> 01:50:34,134
must be flawless.

1021
01:50:55,948 --> 01:50:59,493
Final protocol.
Execute on my order.

1022
01:51:07,084 --> 01:51:10,045
{y:i}[Panicked Chattering]{y}

1023
01:51:15,634 --> 01:51:18,637
{y:i}[Engines Thrumming]{y}

1024
01:51:34,403 --> 01:51:36,655
Go inside.

1025
01:51:37,781 --> 01:51:39,741
Are they leaving now?

1026
01:51:39,825 --> 01:51:42,619
Ziza! Go inside!

1027
01:52:22,618 --> 01:52:24,661
[Gasps]

1028
01:52:34,379 --> 01:52:36,632
{y:i}We found this Lensor dead.{y}

1029
01:52:39,218 --> 01:52:42,638
{y:i}[Lord Marshal]{y}
{y:i}Show me his last sight.{y}

1030
01:52:55,067 --> 01:52:56,735
Commander Toal.

1031
01:52:56,818 --> 01:52:58,820
He won't escape twice.

1032
01:54:08,140 --> 01:54:11,268
[Chattering]

1033
01:54:22,946 --> 01:54:24,907
{y:i}[Metallic Slicing Noise]{y}

1034
01:54:28,285 --> 01:54:30,245
{y:i}[Metallic Slicing Noise]{y}

1035
01:54:33,165 --> 01:54:36,251
[Metallic Slicing]

1036
01:54:48,013 --> 01:54:50,182
[Grunts]

1037
01:54:51,183 --> 01:54:54,311
- [Grunts]
- Stay your weapons!

1038
01:54:55,771 --> 01:54:57,773
He came for me.

1039
01:55:24,550 --> 01:55:26,885
{y:i}[Lord Marshal]{y}
{y:i}Consider this;{y}

1040
01:55:31,765 --> 01:55:35,853
{y:i}If you fall here now,{y}

1041
01:55:35,936 --> 01:55:37,855
you'll never rise.

1042
01:55:37,938 --> 01:55:41,066
{y:i}But if you choose another way...{y}

1043
01:55:42,234 --> 01:55:44,403
{y:i}the Necromonger way...{y}

1044
01:55:44,486 --> 01:55:46,989
{y:i}you'll die in due time...{y}

1045
01:55:47,072 --> 01:55:50,826
and rise again in the UnderVerse.

1046
01:56:00,460 --> 01:56:02,671
Go to him.

1047
01:56:10,179 --> 01:56:12,181
It hurts...

1048
01:56:13,182 --> 01:56:15,434
at first.

1049
01:56:15,517 --> 01:56:19,104
But after a while,
the pain goes away,
just as they promise.

1050
01:56:21,523 --> 01:56:24,026
- Are you with me, Kyra?
- There's a moment...

1051
01:56:24,109 --> 01:56:26,528
when you can almost
see the UnderVerse through his eyes.

1052
01:56:27,863 --> 01:56:30,616
It makes it sound perfect...

1053
01:56:30,699 --> 01:56:32,618
a place where anyone
can start over.

1054
01:56:32,701 --> 01:56:35,162
Are you with me, Kyra?

1055
01:56:47,716 --> 01:56:50,135
Convert now...

1056
01:56:50,219 --> 01:56:52,387
or fall forever.

1057
01:56:57,142 --> 01:56:59,436
You killed everything I know.

1058
01:57:04,566 --> 01:57:05,776
Vaako.

1059
01:57:05,817 --> 01:57:07,778
[Grunts]

1060
01:57:07,861 --> 01:57:10,113
Not yet.

1061
01:57:21,667 --> 01:57:24,628
Been a long time
since I've seen my own blood.

1062
01:58:42,915 --> 01:58:45,918
These are his last moments.

1063
01:59:02,518 --> 01:59:05,437
[Grunting]

1064
01:59:05,521 --> 01:59:08,357
Give me your soul.

1065
01:59:13,362 --> 01:59:16,782
- Fuck you!
- [Groans]

1066
01:59:16,865 --> 01:59:19,201
[Growls]

1067
01:59:21,078 --> 01:59:22,663
[Grunts]

1068
01:59:27,417 --> 01:59:29,294
[Yells]

1069
01:59:45,769 --> 01:59:48,063
[Grunting]

1070
02:00:05,372 --> 02:00:07,416
[Grunts]

1071
02:00:08,834 --> 02:00:11,295
[Grunting]

1072
02:00:22,097 --> 02:00:24,349
You're not the one to bring me down.

1073
02:00:25,350 --> 02:00:26,810
[Groans]

1074
02:00:36,361 --> 02:00:38,447
[Gasps]

1075
02:00:41,533 --> 02:00:43,285
[Groans]

1076
02:00:43,327 --> 02:00:46,079
Now! Kill the beast
while he's wounded!

1077
02:00:56,465 --> 02:00:59,301
[Exhales Deeply]

1078
02:01:00,677 --> 02:01:03,680
[Groaning]

1079
02:01:03,764 --> 02:01:06,808
Help me, Vaako. Kill him.

1080
02:01:14,441 --> 02:01:15,776
Vaako?

1081
02:01:20,447 --> 02:01:22,449
Forgive me.

1082
02:01:22,533 --> 02:01:24,201
Flawless.

1083
02:01:55,065 --> 02:01:57,568
[Gasps]
No.

1084
02:02:03,615 --> 02:02:07,035
No-o-o!
[Echoing]

1085
02:02:07,077 --> 02:02:10,205
Now what would be
the odds of that?

1086
02:02:23,177 --> 02:02:25,762
I thought you were dead.

1087
02:02:28,015 --> 02:02:30,559
Are you with me, Kyra?

1088
02:02:32,644 --> 02:02:35,230
[Sighs]
I was always with you.

1089
02:02:37,566 --> 02:02:39,568
I was.

1090
02:04:03,110 --> 02:04:05,445
You keep what you kill.

